 Certainly! Below is the SPARQL query for DBpedia to find the films directed by Garry Marshall in which Julia Roberts starred:

```sparql
PREFIX dbo: <http://dbpedia.org/ontology/>
PREFIX dbr: <http://dbpedia.org/resource/>

SELECT ?film WHERE {
  ?film dbo:director dbr:Garry_Marshall ;
        dbo:starring dbr:Julia_Roberts .
}
```

This query retrieves the films (`?film`) that have Garry Marshall as the director (`dbo:director dbr:Garry_Marshall`) and Julia Roberts as a starring actor (`dbo:starring dbr:Julia_Roberts`).

 Sure, I can help with that. Below is a SPARQL query for DBpedia to retrieve all islands that belong to Japan:

```sparql
PREFIX dbo: <http://dbpedia.org/ontology/>
PREFIX dbr: <http://dbpedia.org/resource/>
PREFIX dbp: <http://dbpedia.org/property/>

SELECT ?island ?islandLabel
WHERE {
  ?island dbo:location dbr:Japan ;
          rdf:type dbo:Island .
  SERVICE wikibase:label { bd:serviceParam wikibase:language "[AUTO_LANGUAGE],en". }
}
```

This query selects all resources that are of type `dbo:Island` and are located in Japan (`dbr:Japan`). The `SERVICE wikibase:label` is used to get the labels of the islands in the preferred language.

 Certainly! Here's the SPARQL query for DBpedia to retrieve all Danish movies:

```sparql
PREFIX dbo: <http://dbpedia.org/ontology/>
PREFIX dbr: <http://dbpedia.org/resource/>
PREFIX dct: <http://purl.org/dc/terms/>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>

SELECT ?movie ?movieLabel WHERE {
  ?movie dct:subject dbr:Category:Danish_films ;
         rdf:type dbo:Film .
  SERVICE wikibase:label { bd:serviceParam wikibase:language "[AUTO_LANGUAGE],en". }
}
```

This query selects all resources (`?movie`) that are of type `dbo:Film` and are categorized under `dbr:Category:Danish_films`. The `SERVICE wikibase:label` provides the labels for the movies in the preferred language.
